rComments: I'll admit the grading criteria was VERY abstract, but Dr. Preston was one of the most interesting professors I've had at U of T. To be fair, Dramaturgy is a very abstract concept.

She was very unprepared for class. She did not have effective lesson plans and brought guest speakers as often as she could to avoid teaching. All course content, guest speakers, projects, and assignments had very little connection to drama, theatre, or the performing arts. The syllabus was poorly planned and uninteresting.
